Part 1. Election To Expense Certain Property Under Section 179. Note: If you have any listed property, complete Part 5 before you complete Part 1. Line 1. Maximum amount (see instructions).
Line 2. Total cost of section 179 property placed in service (see instructions).
Line 3. Threshold cost of section 179 property before reduction in limitation (see instructions).
Line 4. Reduction in limitation. Subtract line 3 from line 2. If zero or less, enter zero.
Line 5. Dollar limitation for tax year. Subtract line 4 from line 1. If zero or less, enter zero. If married filing separately, see instructions.
Line 6. Item 1. (a) Description of property.
Line 6. Item 1. (b) Cost (business use only).
Line 6. Item 1. (c) Elected cost.
Line 6. Item 2. (a).
Line 6. Item 2. (b).
Line 6. Item 2. (c).
Line 7. Listed property. Enter the amount from line 29.
Line 8. Total elected cost of section 179 property. Add amounts in column (c), lines 6 and 7.
Line 9. Tentative deduction. Enter the smaller of line 5 or line 8.
Line 10. Carryover of disallowed deduction from line 13 of your 2012 Form 4562.
Line 11. Business income limitation. Enter the smaller of business income (not less than zero) or line 5 (see instructions).
Line 12. Section 179 expense deduction. Add lines 9 and 10, but do not enter more than line 11.
Line 13. Carryover of disallowed deduction to 2014. Add lines 9 and 10, less line 12. Note: Do not use Part 2 or Part 3 below for listed property. Instead, use Part 5.

Part 2. Special Depreciation Allowance and Other Depreciation. (Do not include listed property.) (See instructions.) Line 14. Special depreciation allowance for qualified property (other than listed property) placed in service during the tax year (see instructions).
Line 15. Property subject to section 168(f)(1) election.
Line 16. Other depreciation (including A C R S).
Line 17. MACRS deductions for assets placed in service in tax years beginning before 2013.
Part 4. Summary (see instructions). Line 21. Listed property. Enter amount from line 28.

Line 22. Total. Add amounts from line 12, lines 14 through 17, lines 19 and 20 in column (g), and line 21. Enter here and on the appropriate lines of your return. Partnerships and S corporations - see instructions.
Line 23. For assets shown above and placed in service during the current year, enter the portion of the basis attributable to section 263 A costs.
Line 25. Special depreciation allowance for qualified listed property placed in service during the tax year and used more than 50 percent in a qualified business use (see instructions).
Line 28. Add amounts in column (h), lines 25 through 27. Enter here and on line 21, page 1.
Line 29. Add amounts in column (i), line 26. Enter here and on line 7, page 1.
Line 43. Amortization of costs that began before your 2013 tax year.
Line 44. Total. Add amounts in column (f). See the instructions for where to report.
